caption: Staff was stellar.  Food was fantastic. We'll be back for sure!!!

After work, I was in the mood to try a restaurant new to me and I think I just found a neighborhood favorite for myself.  I called in my order and picked it up.  From what I saw, they do have a small patio for dining.  Every person I came in contact with was very friendly from a server who happened to be coming out the door to service a table to another person who gave me the bill.  I ordered the seafood linguini pasta.  The guy over the phone mentioned they could change the pasta to a different one if I liked but I chose to stick with linguini.  The dish was absolutely fantastic!  It was not heavy with cream and other sauces most other restaurants.  There was just something so authentic and plain delicious about the dish.  It made me feel that I was eating a true Italian dish.  Anyway, as you can tell, I would order again.  I also ordered the ricotta cheesecake for dessert.  It's different than what I'm used to (meaning no Graham cracker crust or any crust for that matter) but I still enjoyed.  You can tell it was homemade and could truly taste the ricotta.  I'm eating there again tonight.  Yes, it was that darn good.  They have a 3 course special for $30 so why not?  Highly recommend Sofi!
We went here for dinner after Alvin Alley. Its within walking distance of the theater and it is FANTASTIC! THE SERVICE? Excellent. THE FOOD? Outstanding!

I'm giving it 3 stars because the company I was with enjoyed it, so maybe, just maybe my palet did not appreciate the food as well as it should of, but my friends commented "it's not on are short list of places to return to"

Had a reservation. Was seated 65 mins after reservation. Only one staff member seemed to care about the inconvenience. Manager tried to accommodate with champagne and was apologetic. Food was fantastic and our actual waiter was wonderful.
Nice atmosphere, kind service, delicious food (& desserts!).

Excellent food. Highly recommended. In the land of COVID, things have changed a lot for restaurants. Making great food is no longer enough - it has to be great when you get it home (carry out). We enjoyed our meal this evening immensely. Carpaccio, boar pasta, focaccia, burrata...all excellent and packed for the walk home. Thank you Sofi for nailing it, we'll be back for sure.
It was like heaven 😊

Sofi is my favorite Italian restaurant in Chicago. I’ve tried many options on their menu and have never had a bad meal here. Their gnocchi in particular is delicious, I appreciate how flavorful it is without being too heavy. This is a great date night spot

1. This is NORTHERN ITALIAN, so no spaghetti and meatballs 2. This isn't a "pasta by the pound with red lead" joint 3. They don't serve pizza  Northern Italian is lighter in flavors and more subtle. Risotto, lighter than air gnocchi and home made pastas.  The food here is excellent and far closer to what you will get in Italy than most in Chicago. Artichokes and fontina cheese with truffle, outstanding beef carpaccio and a delicious grilled octopus with potato and pesto.  Next we had (party of 6) homemade pumpkin ravioli and gnocchi with porcini mushrooms. Absolutely home made and delicate raviolis surrounded the pumpkin filling with sage, butter and a touch of tomato sauce. The gnocchi were soft pillowy dumplings and they weren't shy with the marvelous porcini.  I had the Veal Osso Bucco with Risotto Milanese. One of the best I've ever had. Absolutely tender and flavorful with perfect risotto. Have enough for my lunch tomorrow!  This really is an excellent restaurant. Wish the wine list had a bit more depth, but the Barbera d'Alba was delicious. They make a SOLID Negroni as well.
Always the best! Great service, food, and ambiance. I love having this restaurant in the neighborhood, and it’s a go-to for bringing guests when you want an intimate atmosphere.
The staff did a fantastic job and the food was excellent!

italian food here - super tasty. had a sister come into town and asked me to take her here again. feels similar to a restaurant in new york i loved.

Great Italian food at Sofi. Had dinner this past Saturday at Sofi, and it was delicious. And the staff was exceptional. I live in the building that this restaurant is in, and I see that they are always cleaning, so I felt safe to go there.
It’s like a bit of heaven has touched earth.I would give this Restaurant more than 5 stars if I could.
A favorite location for delicious Italian food.
Great Italian food, nice outdoor patio. I had seafood stew, great bread, friendly waiters, excellent wine.

Sofi was such a surprise! It’s a little Italian escape in Chicago. I love Rome for it’s alleyways with little restaurants and Sofi has this same feel. The service and food are both great! The outdoor patio is nice, and inside is nice too. I love this place and I highly recommend it!

Our new favorite restaurant. Food is delicious, very classy place and ambiance.  Outside patio is very nice, with the one of the prettiest streets in Chicago-Printers Row (Dearborn st). If something's not on the menu, they will make it for you. We travel to Italy often and this is feels like a piece of Rome in the middle of Printers Row.

I just love this hidden gem. This place specializes in Tuscan and Northern Italian dishes, it’s not your typical Chicago red-sauce heavy spot. It’s lighter, and very fresh with an emphasis on great taste and preparation over portion size. Also has a small but very well thought out wine list. Great outdoor seating along Dearborn in Printer’s Row and a cozy interior too. This is my go-to for Italian in Chicago and often the place my wife and I visit when celebrating. We have taken many other people here and they are usually blown away.

Sweet place, interesting menu, good service but the shrimp tasted old (fishy) and the ravioli we chose was pretty flavorless. I'd try Sofi again but ordering different items (they too the shrimp off of our bill and were very gracious)
Great neighborhood restaurant. Great food, wonderful staff.
Nice Italian place in walking distance and the service and food was top line.
Nice folks, good selection, solid food. Nice to be able to dine outside on Printers Row

One of the best meals I have had in a long time! My wife and I ate on the patio. Incredible service. Extremely attentive without being overbearing or pushy. I had the Tagliatelle Bolognese and it was so fresh and flavorful. Exactly how my Nonno makes it - who is from Northern Italy! My wife had the Orecchiette Pugliesi. I tried a few bites of her's and it was even better than my meal! All in all, you can't go wrong with either choice. Thank you Sofi Restaurant for everything. We will be back very soon!

Me and my girlfriend are residents of Printers Square. She’s been here once so we decided to go try it last night. The staff acted like they wish were weren’t there and were incredibly rude. A staff member begrudgingly took down our information to call us when a table was ready, yet told us two different wait times. Turns out it didn’t matter, since they never called us. Like, never called us with a table being ready. Why take our number down at all? We have never gone anywhere and been treated so low class. Will not be returning, would not recommend. Would give zero stars if I could.
Love this place. Been here at least a dozen times and have never had a bad meal. The staff are also great!

After so long without going to a restaurant, I was so excited to dine out! Got to go celebrate my birthday at Sofi and if was great. Food was really good overall, the only thing is was ok was the gnocchi. But the scallops with prosciutto in a lobster bisque sauce was to die for. They were also really kind and brought me a tiramisu to sing happy birthday! That's one of my favorite desserts, so I was super happy!
They offer a large variety of delicious food. I enjoy dining here. Staff members are always very nice, prices are convenient and the spot is always neat.

We dined at this cozy, Printers Row spot before attending a show in the South Loop. The service was great and the food was unique and outstanding. The grilled mozzarella and prosciutto appetizer was unique and tasty. My spouse had the grilled scallops and shrimp on fennel (a special that night) that looked fantastic. My saffron risotto with mild sausage ragout was amazing.

We asked to be seated outside which was nice for people watching as people strolled by, many with their dogs. I ordered a rose which was delicious. We enjoyed their bread offering with olive oil and ordered carpaccio and an interesting dish of zucchini fritters with ham as appetisers. Both choices were excellent. Similarly our entrees, lobster ravioli and chicken parmigiana were very good. We shared a tiramisu for dessert which was excellent

Excellent, Excellent,  Excellent food,  atmosphere and staff.  Great drinks.  Ask for the specials. I had the Sea Bass with,  calamari,  clams and muscles. Pure Awesomeness is how I describe the sex on the beach drink.

I was hoping for a cream sauce or something with flavor. My dinner partner is well versed in all regions of Italian food. Not once did he comment on his dish, which is rare for him. It was a wonderful summer evening, so my friend and I decided to dine outside at Sofi. We each had the Tagliatelle Bolognese and a bottle of red wine. The wines are not familiar, so let your server help you select one. Ours suggested a better one than we originally ordered. It was a little more, but great. The portions were more than ample, so we didn't miss a salad or appetizer. I also received a special birthday tiramisu. It is a hidden gem in Chicago.

I love Italian cuisine and wine! Last night I asked for a Sangiovese. They didn't have it. The waiter offered a wine that I had never experienced, he brought out a tasting, it was decent. Before consuming the glass of wine my guest and I inquired about the price point. In general, Sangiovese is not an inexpensive wine however we weren't expecting $27.00 per glass. The waiter responded to our surprise by offering to remove the charge, though we never indicated that's what we were seeking. We received the check and noticed that the charge was not removed so we asked about it and the waiter said, "Oh my boss said I can not do it". We were not informed at any moment during the service conversations with our waiter that he was rescinding his offer. We asked for the manager and a man came to our table to totally insult us as if we were attempting to consume without paying. We are embarrassed for this establishment and hope to encourage them to change their attitude. The tip alone would have been more than the cost of the glass of wine and simply not worth ruining our dinner date.

Sofi is a quaint Italian restaurant on Printer's Row just a few blocks off Michigan. Excellent selection of Northern Italian dishes including hand-made pasta with authentic sauces that are difficult to find outside of the Tuscan countryside. The pasta alone makes it a unique experience in the Downtown Chicago area. Other notable dishes include the Branzino (available as the whole fish or filleted) and the Osso Buco.  Wine selection is appropriate for the menu.  Overall, reasonably priced and an excellent value. Other reviewers have complained about the service, but our waiter was both helpful and polite.   Indoor and outdoor seating as weather permits.

Great ambiance and the servers were so knowledgeable and kind. The food was fantastic and the wine list was extensive and reasonably priced. It seemed like a well established restaurant and the dim lights created a warm environment to spend time with your friends, family and/or significant other. Definitely recommend this place to anyone!

Mentioned politely to the waiter that my steak is cold and he snatched the plate from under me and walked away, not saying a word. A few minutes later another waiter came out and slipped the plate back under me with the steak now greyer and dryer! I had 2 bites and left the plate. I am not a fussy eater so leaving food is saying a lot!  To be fair the restaurant atmosphere is quite cosy. We had hoped the food would be decent so we can come regularly as we live close by. Besides the snatching of plates, the serving staff were generally quite friendly, but the overall experience was terrible.

Sofi is excellent. I've been twice in a month and plan to return again soon. The restaurant is very pleasant, and the staff are quite accommodating and extremely knowledgeable about the menu and how dishes are prepared. I had a gnocchi special the first time, which was delicious. This time, I had the Orecchiette Pugliesi, which was authentic to the traditional dish I had in Bari, Italy. Wine prices are very reasonable, and there's a nice variety. Highly recommend.

Underwhelming after having high hopes.  Food: The food is very bland. The burrata is okay, skip the fava beans antipasti all together and the pasta and sauce just don’t quite create any feelings. They have some serious work to do on preparation, combination and plating.  Ambiance: The walls and glass windows really echo people’s conversation and it was extremely loud when we ate, far from a quiet little restaurant feel I was expecting. My guest was embarrassed on my behalf for my pick.  Service: One server covered an entire floor of about 40 people and 7-8 tables and one assist. Our empty dishes sat, at times, for half hour on an otherwise small table before getting picked up. Our server sounded very stressed upon request to understand the pasta selection and we only saw him 4 times in 3 hours. Don’t know what financials look like here but adding another person for evening traffic would be a good idea.  Highly disappointed and will not return here. If you’re a big Italian food fan, heading to West Loop area would be your best dollars spent - Monteverde, Formento’s, Piccolo Sogno, even pizza place Forno Roso (great burrata) is the way to go.

The service was slow, but I think that is part of the experience here. They want you to enjoy your meal and take your time. They have a decent wine selection. The bread that comes out before the meal is delicious. We ordered the beef tenderloin and the bolognese. The beef was not hot when it arrived, but otherwise tasted good. It came with artichoke hearts that were way too oily, but otherwise good. The bolognese was outstanding. We also ordered dessert. The creme brulee was alright - nothing special, but good. The "ricotta cheesecake" was horrible. It was like hot, mealy ricotta cheese. Avoid that dessert please! Overall we had a nice time, but I would not necessarily go back.

We ordered fried zucchini blossoms, salsiccia and rapini and half orders of tagliatelle bolognese and cacio e pepe....and got to taste the tiramisu as a birthday treat. All made fresh daily and it shows. Wish we had caught the waiters name- was great! Will be back!

Their menu clearly says "20 % gratuities will be add to party of 6 or more before taxes", but apparently they're a little fast and loose with that "6", because they charged our group of 5 this automatic 20%.  Our waiter did a bad job though, and probably knew he was going to get a bad tip. So maybe just was just trying to pull a fast one to salvage the situation.  Truffles tasted like peanuts, pasta sauce tasted no better than Ragu, and the staff's fake Italian accents got annoying after a while.

Nothing can be more disappointing than selecting a restaurant for a dinner and having it turn into one of the worst culinary affairs ever. Waiter came by finally, said bread was coming and we had water. He returned and took wine order, no bread. Still no bread this is now fifteen minutes plus, finally wine arrived as did bread. Ahh it was not worth the wait for the bread, insipid would be kind, but needed some sustenance. He returns and we give order, he goes away, comes back and does not remember order, repeat it Salads arrive, and are decent. Wait at least 30 minutes for food and it comes out cold. Oh wait two of them come out cold and one of the four was wrong. One eaten, an entre that had no veggies or starch side, others wait... Two cold ones return and seemed to be recooked and/or had hot water run over them. One was actually good. We mentioned to our waiter that this was unacceptable, he disavowed any responsibility for it. Blaming front of house, and kitchen. He did give us a bottle of wine and not charge us for one we ordered. Also took one of the cold entrees off bill. He was apologetic and asked what could make it right, we replied nothing at this point. Let it be known that other sections had  turned over tables twice, but he said it wasn't his fault. See prior comments. We really wanted this to be a great dinner but it failed so badly that we might grab some Dunkin Donuts or Subway to ease the pain. Very sad, very disappointing, very hungry.

Disappointed  and still hungry.  Our waiter just didn't have it together.  Long wait to order, long wait for starters, longer wait for entrees.  Meanwhile, tables in another section came and went.  My entree and another were cold and sent back.   Replacements not much better.  Two others had a good entree that was hot.   I asked that my uneaten entree be taken off the bill and it was.  Still looking for a good Italian restaurant in Chicago.  This wasn't it.
Our server was very charming and very hospitable. One of my favorite places to go here in Chicago. Give this place a try. You will love their wine selection. Best Italian food I ever tasted too!

One of my favorite Italian restaurants in Chicago. The food is delicious, the atmosphere is charming, and the owner is a friendly man who often comes to customer tables to check on the service. Some of the best asparagus soup I've ever had, and a lovely wine selection.

Great Italian food and service!
Wonderful old school Italian. Great service and delicious food.

Excellent service!  The food was amazing.  I had an asparagus and tarreggio risotto.  They will do half portions which is nice.  The arugula salad with Parmesan had a nice vinaigrette.  It was a little jewel.
Very good
Very good Italian cuisine. Service was second to none.
Excellent food and service
Our food was extremely cold and lacked any type of seasoning.
Amazing dishes...custom no problem@
Good service but expensive food for what it is. Setting is neutral. I took an appetizer with zucchini flowers that was disappointing. My pasta were a bit too cooked.
Great place. Waiter was super helpful & friendly. Food was very good and well priced. From out of town and very happy we decided to go here. : )
Horrible!
Loved this restaurant. We are outside so we could enjoy the atmospere of down town Chicago. And the food and wine was fantastic. And there was no wait to be seated.

My wife and I stayed in Chicago for two weeks and has been to a lot of restaurant from River North to South. Sofi without argument is the best true Italian restaurant that we’ve been to in Chicago. Charming atmosphere, nice wine recommendation and excellent service from Mr Michele. The skewed pork Branzino Whole Forno and Obsobuco was unbelievably magic and dessert was definitely tempting. Excellent. Will go back. Thank you Sofi

Ordered linguini white wine clam sauce but got spaghetti (which is default on menu) ... decided to keep it and it was competent with great sauce/seasoning but would have been better if the order was right.  Tirama Su was excellent. Recommended Pinot Grigio also good.  Service attentive but not pushy/hovering. Quick turnaround from order to table.  If this place was in Denver, would eat there every week as they have lots of menu options to explore.  A new Chicago fave for sure.  4 stars

The price was good for the food, even in Chicago. The server was friendly and helpful. The pasta I ordered has a nice sauce and the bread served as an appetizer was fresh. Portions aren't too big. If you're not to hungry get a half meal.

I wish Sofi were better, since we lived so close, but its reach exceeds its grasp.  I appreciate the huge menu, and the the additional daily specials which almost always contain something out of the ordinary.  But, at every visit, there is always one or two dishes that miss the mark. Tonight it was the farfalle with duck ragu that had almost no duck in it.  The service is relaxed - sometimes inattentive.  It's our neighborhood Italian place, and you can get a good meal if you order carefully- but watch out for the too frequent misses.
Nice place. Excellent rack of lamb
Every time I go here, I feel so grateful for it. They are amazing in every way!
(Translated by Google) Very good restaurant, nice dishes with respect for the ingredients.  (Original) Zeer goede restaurant, fijne gerechten met respect voor de ingrediënten.
Best Italian in the area! Authentic atmosphere, friendly staff, delicious food.. eating there, especially al fresco in summer time, is a true pleasure!
Very good food. Fast service. Attentive polite people! Awesome wine.Quiant feeling. Not overpriced!

Great place, recommend it! Leek and mushroom soup was very good. Spaghetti with clams in white wine sauce with garlic was excellent. Not too much sauce, could taste the pasta, which was great, along with the clams. Panna Cota for dessert was creamy and sweet, loved it. And their bread was very fresh and good. Nice atmosphere and friendly attentive staff.

A friendly, delicious place to bring friends and family! The atmosphere is warm and inviting, the service is attentive but not pushy, and the food is classic regional Italian with a few well-chosen surprises thrown in. Definitely a great choice for a night out on the town!
Very nice authentic Italian food.

Amazing place, always seems not busy. Incredibly professional and knowledgeable staff. Only complaint is the god awful 90s pop they were playing. It might just be me, but somehow Backstreet Boys, Garth brooks and sugar ray just don't seem to add much to northern Italian cuisine
I could hear then preparing the veal. Those are the good sounds.
Horrible pasta, wasn't cooked enough, still very hard, not even close to 'al dente', also skimpy with the meat
Amazing food and a perfect atmosphere for a big family dinner! The servers were absolute professionals. This is one of my favorite restaurants in the area.
Very good food. Doesn't ever seem to get packed.
Food was solid and had great service.

We happened to find this fantastic little restaurant on Google maps on a visit to Chicago. We were so impressed with the food and service we came back for a second night the next day. Highly recommended!!!!

This syne first time my wife and I have been to Chicago and this place made our visit perfect. Great food I would recommend to anyone. But the best part was our pleasant waiter Richard aka Bove. He was very professional and knowledgeable and made us feel at home in this city! Thanks you! Will stop by next time we are here.

The service was outstanding, from the kindhearted server to the attentive waitstaff.. I was floored with the ambiance, service, and food. I had the lobster ravioli... Maybe the best I've ever had. The sauce was to die for. Not over priced at all. If you are in Chicago, I definitely recommend going.

Adorable little restaurant. The food is absolutely amazing (I've been here 3 times, had something different every time, and loved it all. And you can get half orders of the pasta, which is very convenient!). The waitstaff is friendly and doesn't rush you. We just went before the ballet and let them know that we needed to be out within an hour, and they were great about promptly serving us. I recommend this to anyone looking for a quality, authentic Italian meal.

Terrible service, perhaps the staff thought my girlfriend and I were not "paying customers". Upon arriving we were asked if we had reservations because the 4 out of 40 tables were taken so they must of been terribly busy. We got seated outside at our request. Then, waited 20 mins for the waiter to bring water, another 20 mins for a glass of wine and after another 20 mins we finally had the chance to order an app. After 30 mins waiting for the "polenta" app (that takes 10mins to cook) we had enough and walked out. So, we sat outside for an hour and a half for a glass of wine and for the waiter to be very inattentive. Oh, but the nice older couple dressed nicely enjoyed  very quick service and received their drinks, appetizer and salad before we had our appetizer. Terrible that they treated us (we were dressed a little more casual than then the average table) like we some punk kids. Never again.
One of the better dinners I have take.
GREAT food & service!
Wonderful.
